-- Defending Champion Kvitova Advances to Fourth Round at Wimbledon
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-06-30T13:17:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-30/defending-champion-kvitova-advances-to-fourth-round-at-wimbledon.html
 Defending champion Petra Kvitova
beat Varvara Lepchenko of the U.S. 6-1, 6-0 to advance to the
fourth round of the Wimbledon tennis championships.  Kvitova, of the Czech Republic, will next face No. 24
Francesca Schiavone of Italy, who beat Klara Zakopalova of the
Czech Republic 6-0, 6-4 at the All England Club in London.  Anna Ivanovic, the 14th seed from Serbia, was a 3-6, 6-3,
6-4 winner over Germany’s  Julia Goerges . In the men’s draw,
unseeded American  Brian Baker  beat France’s Benoit Paire 6-4,
4-6, 6-1, 6-3 to move into the fourth round.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  